GWT is more and more looking like the way of the future for simply creating ajax apps.
It would be very cool if confluence provided plugin points for GWT based plugins. Not entirely sure what this would consist of though, but there is obviously some plumbing needed to run GWT within a confluence page - so better to have this standardised than repeated for every plugin.

