This is regarding how a user navigates the wiki.

You have a built in panel that shows all the children of a page, so that makes it a nice structured way to go from father to sun. But why not also show the Siblings? Think of a use case where you use the wiki to write product documentation. The user wants to navigate the documentation like he does chm file. He can go all 4 ways (down,up,left,right, where up is father, down is to a sun, and sides is to the siblings).

Either enhance the existing children control, or add a new control that in a given page, shows me the 360 deg view of navigation...

