I've been making use of the Blogger API plugin lately and since switching to a GUI blog editor (ecto) have been hit a few times by submitting a post using <ul><li> and <b> etc. which get escaped and rendered directly in the blog post in confluence.

It would be good if the blogger api plugin translation basic HTML markup into the relevent wiki markup:

* Bold, Underline, Strikethrough
* Ordered and Unordered lists
* <blockquote> to {quote}
* <h1> etc. to h1. etc.

This would make using ecto and other HTML/Rich blogging clients nicer to work with when using confluence.

