When people use the {favpages} macro, not only are they wanting to see their favourite pages, they may actually want to share those favourite pages with their fellow Confluence users.

Unfortunately, when you view a user's personal space and the user's home page includes the {favpages} macro, you're shown your own favourites, not those of the user who is attempting to share them.

Would it be possible to enhance the {favpages} macro to allow for the indication that you want to truly share your favourites, and not just echo back the favourite pages of the viewer?

